  "title": "Project Engineer (Civil / Roadwork) #79717",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Constructions (Roads & Railways)</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Project Engineer (Civil / Roadwork)</strong></li><li>Working Location: Kovan</li><li>Working Hours: Monday – Saturday, 8:30AM – 5:30PM (No need to work on Saturday if no project)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + HP Allowance + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist the Project Manager in planning, coordinating, and executing roadwork projects.</li><li>Supervise site activities, including road construction, pavement works, drainage, and utilities diversion.</li><li>Ensure all works comply with LTA and relevant authority standards, including traffic management requirements.</li><li>Coordinate effectively with consultants, subcontractors, and client representatives to ensure smooth project delivery.</li><li>Review drawings, method statements, and technical submissions to ensure accuracy and compliance.</li><li>Monitor site progress, cost, and quality to ensure completion within schedule and specifications.</li><li>Prepare progress reports, maintain proper site documentation, and support inspections by authorities.</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the department head.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering, Structural Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Proven experience in roadwork projects (LTA project exposure is an advantage).</li><li>Strong knowledge of road construction methods, traffic management, drainage, and utilities coordination.</li><li>Good understanding of construction methodologies, project scheduling, and safety compliance.</li><li>Familiarity with local authority submission processes is an added advantage.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79717 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
